#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/wasm_audio_worklets.rst:180
msgid "Synchronizing audio thread with the main thread"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/wasm_audio_worklets.rst:182
msgid ""
"Wasm Audio Worklets API builds on top of the Emscripten Wasm Workers "
"feature. This means that the Wasm Audio Worklet thread is modeled as if it "
"was a Wasm Worker thread."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/wasm_audio_worklets.rst:184
msgid ""
"To synchronize information between an Audio Worklet Node and other threads "
"in the application, there are three options:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/wasm_audio_worklets.rst:186
msgid ""
"Leverage the Web Audio \"AudioParams\" model. Each Audio Worklet Processor "
"type is instantiated with a custom defined set of audio parameters that can "
"affect the audio computation at sample precise accuracy. These parameters "
"are passed in the ``params`` array into the audio processing function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/wasm_audio_worklets.rst:188
msgid ""
"The main browser thread that created the Web Audio context can adjust the "
"values of these parameters whenever desired. See `MDN function: "
"setValueAtTime <https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/AudioParam/"
"setValueAtTime>`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/wasm_audio_worklets.rst:190
msgid ""
"Data can be shared with the Audio Worklet thread using GCC/Clang lock-free "
"atomics operations, Emscripten atomics operations and the Wasm Worker API "
"thread synchronization primitives. See :ref:`wasm_workers` for more "
"information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../source/docs/api_reference/wasm_audio_worklets.rst:192
msgid ""
"Utilize the ``emscripten_audio_worklet_post_function_*()`` family of event "
"passing functions. These functions operate similar to the "
"``emscripten_wasm_worker_post_function_*()`` functions. They enable a "
"``postMessage()`` style of communication, where the audio worklet thread and "
"the main browser thread can send messages (function call dispatches) to each "
"other."
msgstr ""

